  <H2>Refractory Periods</H2>

  <Body>The gating variable dynamics explain the refractory periods that limit action potential firing rate:</Body>

  <Body>Absolute refractory period: Immediately after an action potential, sodium channels are inactivated (h ≈ 0). No stimulus, regardless of strength, can trigger another action potential because insufficient sodium channels are available for activation. Duration: ~1 ms.</Body>

  <Body>Relative refractory period: As h recovers, some sodium channels become available, but not all. Additionally, residual K⁺ conductance (elevated n) makes the membrane harder to depolarize. A stronger-than-normal stimulus can trigger an action potential, but with reduced amplitude and increased threshold. Duration: several ms.</Body>

