  <H2>Parameter Sensitivity and Model Behavior</H2>

  <Body>The HH model's behavior is sensitive to its parameters, providing insight into how channel properties shape neuronal excitability:</Body>

  <Body>• Increasing ḡ_Na: Lower threshold, larger action potential amplitude, can lead to repetitive firing</Body>
  <Body>• Decreasing ḡ_Na: Higher threshold, reduced amplitude, eventual failure of action potential generation</Body>
  <Body>• Increasing ḡ_K: Faster repolarization, larger undershoot, shorter refractory period</Body>
  <Body>• Decreasing ḡ_K: Slower repolarization, prolonged action potentials, possible plateau potentials</Body>
  <Body>• Temperature: Rate constants scale with temperature (Q₁₀ ≈ 3), so action potentials are faster at higher temperatures</Body>

