  <H2>Looking Forward</H2>

  <Body>The Hodgkin-Huxley model provides the foundation for understanding neuronal excitability, but it is just the beginning. In subsequent lessons, we will explore:</Body>

  <Body>• Reduced models: FitzHugh-Nagumo and other simplifications that capture essential dynamics</Body>
  <Body>• Bifurcation analysis: How HH dynamics relate to different excitability types</Body>
  <Body>• Channel diversity: Models with additional channel types (A-type K⁺, Ca²⁺, etc.)</Body>
